{"/service/ndnp/nbu/batch_nbu_housesparrow_ver01/data/sn81002003/00517014217/1958040501/1001.xml":{"full_text":"VIRGINIA, MINN., Mesabi Daily\nNews: \"If we can in this fast-moving\nage have solid economie development\nwithout th\u00e8 corrosive influence of in\nflation we ought to begin to find it\nout. Unless we start soon to try we\nmay discover one day that inflation\nis taken for granted by management,\nlabor and everybody else as an in\nescapable companion to our economie\nprogress. Then is hastened th\u00e8 day\nwhen th\u00e8 house of cards will col\nlapse.\u201d I\nWALTHAM, MASS. News-Tribune:\n\"The talk is of tax cuts as a pump\npriming device at th\u00e8 national level\nto cope with th\u00e8 recession. This is\ndeficit financing of th\u00e8 most extreme\nnature, in which all possibility of a\npay-as-you-go policy is chucked out\nth\u00e8 window. How can th\u00e8 govern\nili ent expeqt its citizens to be thrifty\nwhen it gives no heed to tomorrow's\nbills?\"\nNEW PHILADELPHIA, OHIO,\nDaily Times: \"The communist world\ndoes a great deal of blatant advertis\ning of its alleged charms for th\u00e8\nmasses of humanity.\n\"In a recent CBS interview, Mayor\nWilly Brandt of West Berlin said\nthat every day 300 to 500 East Ger\nmans cross into West Berlin as refu\ngees. Since 1950 th\u00e8 stream has\nmounted to more than one million.\nIf Communist lands are such a mag\nnificent haven for humanity, why\ndon't people stay? You\u2019ll never see\nth\u00e8 answer to that in th\u00e8 Kremlin\u2019s\nads.\u201d\nRIVERTON, WYO., Ranger: '\u201cGov\nernment has grown so large that it is\nbeyond comprehension, incapable of\nself-regulation and bent on perpetua\ntion of its various components.\n\"People fear th\u00e8 thought of th\u00e8 un\nwieldly monster attaching even one\nof its tentacles onto th\u00e8 public\nschools, no matter how innocent and\ntrivial th\u00e8 initial attachment seems\nto be.\"\nNORWALK, CONN., Hour: \"The\nguiding spirit of th\u00e8 recovery, as th\u00e8\nPresident sees it, is not a crash pro\ngram by th\u00e8 Government. Rather, th\u00e8\ngovernment is leading off with enough\nto encourage private ejiterprise. Busi\nness is there \u2018for those who believe in\nit and prepare for it.\u2019 The recovery\nwill be sounder and more lasting that\nway.\u201d\nv\nBEDFORD, IND., Daily Times\nMail: \"Education is th\u00e8 most selfish\nthing in th\u00e8 world. The only per\nson who can give it to you is you.\nTeachers can lead, suggest, cajole,\neven browbeat, but they can\u2019t make\nyou learn. That you do alone.\u201d\nDelegates to th\u00e8 latest convention\nof th\u00e8 American Farm Bureau Fed\nMACARONI\nSPAGHETTI\nNOODLES\neration approved a resolution oppos\ning compulsory unionism and favor\ning a national tight-to-worit law. The\nresolution States: \"No person should\nbe deprived of his right to work be\ncause of membership or lack of mem\nbership in any organization.\u201d\nGRAYSON, KY., Joumal-Enquirer:\n\u2018In applying for dlvoroe, a Brisbane,\nAustralia, man told th\u00e8 court his wife\nmacie him sleep in th\u00e8 barn where\nshe served his meals by throwing\nthem at him, and that she often\nparaded nude in th\u00e8 yard.\u2019\u2014Press re\nport. Some women are harder to live\nwith than others.\u201d\nInvestment\n29th and Farnam\n\nThe location wilh a future. 5 near\nnew business buildings with a brick\n0 unit apartment house. $895 per\nmonth income. Many future possibi\nlities in this choice close-in business\narea.\nHANCOCK REAL ESTATE\nCA. 1068\nAT. 0255\nSINCE 1890\nORTMAN BAKERIES\n1101 SOUTH 24th ST. WE. 6462\nEASTER GREETINGS TO ALL OUR FRIENDS\n\nGRAIN DEALERS MUTUAL\nINSURANCE CO.\n\nFire, Auto, Inland Marine Insurance\ni\n\"Our 56th Year\"\nTel. HA. 9100\n320 Omaha Grain Exchange Building\nANOTHER FIRST FROM YOUR HOME FURNISHINGS MART\nI\n...WOW!!\nWalk on Air At Down-to-Earth Prices\nWe\u2019ll Carpet\n3 ROOMS\n1 HALL\nANY SIZE\nAll for Only.\nFREE\nPADDING (U.S. Waffle)\nINSTALLATION (Tackless)\nOPEN MONDAY and THURSDAY TILL 9 P.M.\nHOME FURNISHINGS MART\n4831\u2018DODGE WA 1100\nNELLA TRADIZIONALE FESTA PRIMAVERILE AUGURIAMO\nA TUTTI: PACE E PROSPERITA\u2019\nOMAHA STEEL\nWORKS\n609 South 48th Street\nTel. GLendale 7222","height":"21072","width":"13452"}}
